        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h2 id="这个是二级标题"><a href="#这个是二级标题" class="headerlink" title="这个是二级标题"></a>这个是二级标题</h2><p>第一次使用Hexo，进行文章的一个上传，并且进行一个Github库的同步。<br><br>摸鱼摸烦了的后果就是这样的……</p><h3 id="这个是三级标题"><a href="#这个是三级标题" class="headerlink" title="这个是三级标题"></a>这个是三级标题</h3><p><img src="/2021/10/25/%E7%AC%AC%E4%B8%80%E7%AF%87%E6%96%87%E7%AB%A0%E4%B8%8A%E4%BC%A0%E6%B5%8B%E8%AF%95/sleepy.jpg" alt="图片标题"><br><br><br><br><br><br><strong>这个是加粗字体</strong>，<em>这个是斜体</em><br><br>这个是一段python代码</p><figure class="highlight python"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br><span class="line">9</span><br><span class="line">10</span><br><span class="line">11</span><br><span class="line">12</span><br><span class="line">13</span><br><span class="line">14</span><br><span class="line">15</span><br><span class="line">16</span><br><span class="line">17</span><br><span class="line">18</span><br><span class="line">19</span><br><span class="line">20</span><br><span class="line">21</span><br><span class="line">22</span><br><span class="line">23</span><br><span class="line">24</span><br><span class="line">25</span><br><span class="line">26</span><br><span class="line">27</span><br><span class="line">28</span><br><span class="line">29</span><br><span class="line">30</span><br><span class="line">31</span><br><span class="line">32</span><br><span class="line">33</span><br><span class="line">34</span><br><span class="line">35</span><br><span class="line">36</span><br><span class="line">37</span><br><span class="line">38</span><br><span class="line">39</span><br><span class="line">40</span><br><span class="line">41</span><br><span class="line">42</span><br><span class="line">43</span><br><span class="line">44</span><br><span class="line">45</span><br><span class="line">46</span><br><span class="line">47</span><br><span class="line">48</span><br><span class="line">49</span><br><span class="line">50</span><br><span class="line">51</span><br><span class="line">52</span><br><span class="line">53</span><br><span class="line">54</span><br><span class="line">55</span><br><span class="line">56</span><br><span class="line">57</span><br><span class="line">58</span><br><span class="line">59</span><br><span class="line">60</span><br><span class="line">61</span><br><span class="line">62</span><br><span class="line">63</span><br><span class="line">64</span><br><span class="line">65</span><br><span class="line">66</span><br><span class="line">67</span><br><span class="line">68</span><br><span class="line">69</span><br><span class="line">70</span><br><span class="line">71</span><br><span class="line">72</span><br><span class="line">73</span><br><span class="line">74</span><br><span class="line">75</span><br><span class="line">76</span><br><span class="line">77</span><br><span class="line">78</span><br><span class="line">79</span><br><span class="line">80</span><br><span class="line">81</span><br><span class="line">82</span><br><span class="line">83</span><br><span class="line">84</span><br><span class="line">85</span><br><span class="line">86</span><br><span class="line">87</span><br><span class="line">88</span><br><span class="line">89</span><br><span class="line">90</span><br><span class="line">91</span><br><span class="line">92</span><br><span class="line">93</span><br><span class="line">94</span><br><span class="line">95</span><br><span class="line">96</span><br><span class="line">97</span><br><span class="line">98</span><br><span class="line">99</span><br><span class="line">100</span><br><span class="line">101</span><br><span class="line">102</span><br><span class="line">103</span><br><span class="line">104</span><br><span class="line">105</span><br><span class="line">106</span><br><span class="line">107</span><br><span class="line">108</span><br><span class="line">109</span><br><span class="line">110</span><br><span class="line">111</span><br><span class="line">112</span><br><span class="line">113</span><br><span class="line">114</span><br><span class="line">115</span><br><span class="line">116</span><br><span class="line">117</span><br><span class="line">118</span><br><span class="line">119</span><br><span class="line">120</span><br><span class="line">121</span><br><span class="line">122</span><br><span class="line">123</span><br><span class="line">124</span><br><span class="line">125</span><br><span class="line">126</span><br><span class="line">127</span><br><span class="line">128</span><br><span class="line">129</span><br><span class="line">130</span><br><span class="line">131</span><br><span class="line">132</span><br><span class="line">133</span><br><span class="line">134</span><br><span class="line">135</span><br><span class="line">136</span><br><span class="line">137</span><br><span class="line">138</span><br><span class="line">139</span><br><span class="line">140</span><br><span class="line">141</span><br><span class="line">142</span><br><span class="line">143</span><br><span class="line">144</span><br><span class="line">145</span><br><span class="line">146</span><br><span class="line">147</span><br><span class="line">148</span><br><span class="line">149</span><br><span class="line">150</span><br><span class="line">151</span><br><span class="line">152</span><br><span class="line">153</span><br><span class="line">154</span><br><span class="line">155</span><br><span class="line">156</span><br><span class="line">157</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="string">&quot;&quot;&quot;</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">This is the feature recognition and feature matching part of the 3DScanner project.</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">python version: 3.8.3</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">opencv version: 4.5.1</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">Author: Jiangeng Sun, Julia Stål</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">Reference:</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">1. https://docs.opencv.org/master/dc/dc3/tutorial_py_matcher.html</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">2. (Chinese) https://zhuanlan.zhihu.com/p/157578594</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">3. (Chinese) https://zhuanlan.zhihu.com/p/56160816</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">4. https://docs.opencv.org/3.4/da/de9/tutorial_py_epipolar_geometry.html</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">&quot;&quot;&quot;</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">import</span> numpy <span class="keyword">as</span> np</span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">import</span> cv2</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">&#x27;&#x27;&#x27;</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">Part 1 </span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">Data loading and parameter adjustment</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">&#x27;&#x27;&#x27;</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># Parameters</span></span><br><span class="line">MIN_MATCH_COUNT = <span class="number">10</span></span><br><span class="line">ratio = <span class="number">0.85</span></span><br><span class="line">ransacReprojThreshold = <span class="number">4</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># Images address. Choose a pair of images to test</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># image_address_1 = &#x27;img/chana1.jpeg&#x27;</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># image_address_2 = &#x27;img/chana2.jpeg&#x27;</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># # Images address. Choose a pair of images to test</span></span><br><span class="line">image_address_1 = <span class="string">&#x27;../blender/renders/render6/1.jpg&#x27;</span></span><br><span class="line">image_address_2 = <span class="string">&#x27;../blender/renders/render6/2.jpg&#x27;</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment">#Had to change the path to this for it to work on my computer /Julia</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment">#image_address_1 = &#x27;blender\\renders\\render6\\1.jpg&#x27;</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment">#image_address_2 = &#x27;blender\\renders\\render6\\2.jpg&#x27;</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># image_address_1 = &#x27;../blender/renders/render6/0001.png&#x27;</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># image_address_2 = &#x27;../blender/renders/render6/0028.png&#x27;</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># load rgb image</span></span><br><span class="line">img_homo_rgb = cv2.imread(image_address_1)</span><br><span class="line">img_homo_train_rgb = cv2.imread(image_address_2)</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># load gray image</span></span><br><span class="line">img_homo = cv2.imread(image_address_1, <span class="number">0</span>)</span><br><span class="line">img_homo_train = cv2.imread(image_address_2, <span class="number">0</span>)</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">&#x27;&#x27;&#x27;</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">Part 2 </span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">Use SIFT to extract features</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">&#x27;&#x27;&#x27;</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># Call SIFT function of OpenCV</span></span><br><span class="line">sift = cv2.SIFT_create()</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># Use SIFT to extract features.</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># **params: kp1,kp2 are keypoints, des1 and des2 are descriptors.</span></span><br><span class="line">kp1, des1 = sift.detectAndCompute(img_homo, <span class="literal">None</span>)</span><br><span class="line">kp2, des2 = sift.detectAndCompute(img_homo_train, <span class="literal">None</span>)</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">&#x27;&#x27;&#x27;</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">Part 3</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">Use Brute-force search to match features</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">Note: I did not find a tutorial on matching feature points using the Best-Bin-First algorithm on the Internet. </span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">      So I tried Brute-force search and FLANN.</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">&#x27;&#x27;&#x27;</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># Call the Brute-force search algorithm or FLANN.</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># These two algorithms are currently popular feature matching algorithms that I can find.</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># Choose one of these two.</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># Brute-force search algorithm(KNN matcher)(Uncomment 52~53 lines of code to use this algorithm)</span></span><br><span class="line">matcher = cv2.BFMatcher()</span><br><span class="line">matches = matcher.knnMatch(des1, des2, k=<span class="number">2</span>)</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># FLANN (Uncomment 56~60 lines of code to use this algorithm)</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># FLANN_INDEX_KDTREE = 0</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># index_params = dict(algorithm=FLANN_INDEX_KDTREE, trees=5)</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># search_params = dict(checks=50)</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># flannbased = cv2.FlannBasedMatcher(index_params, search_params)</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># matches = flannbased.knnMatch(des1, des2, k=2)</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">topmatch = []</span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># Because the k value in KNN is 2, compare the points in image1 with the best and second-match points in image2.</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># m and n represent the best matching point and the second matching point.</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># If the ratio of distance of the best matching point to the second matching point is greater than a threshold,</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># Then we keep this best matching value and consider it to match the point as a good match.</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">for</span> m, n <span class="keyword">in</span> matches:</span><br><span class="line">    <span class="keyword">if</span> m.distance/n.distance &lt; ratio:</span><br><span class="line">        topmatch.append(m)</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">draw_params = <span class="built_in">dict</span>(matchColor=-<span class="number">1</span>, singlePointColor=-<span class="number">1</span>, matchesMask=<span class="literal">None</span>, flags=<span class="number">2</span>)</span><br><span class="line">BeforeRANSAC = cv2.drawMatches(img_homo_rgb, kp1, img_homo_train_rgb, kp2, topmatch, <span class="literal">None</span>, **draw_params)</span><br><span class="line"><span class="built_in">print</span>(<span class="string">&#x27;The number of matching points that have not been processed by RANSAC:&#x27;</span>, <span class="built_in">len</span>(topmatch))</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">&#x27;&#x27;&#x27;</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">Part 4</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">Use RANSAC algorithm to eliminate wrong matching points.</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">&#x27;&#x27;&#x27;</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># If the number of matching points is large enough, then the wrong matching points need to be eliminated.</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># Otherwise, there is no need (because there is no point available after erasing).</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">if</span> <span class="built_in">len</span>(topmatch) &gt; MIN_MATCH_COUNT:</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    <span class="comment"># Reshape the key points for homography matrix calculation.</span></span><br><span class="line">    src_pts = np.float32([kp1[m.queryIdx].pt <span class="keyword">for</span> m <span class="keyword">in</span> topmatch]).reshape(-<span class="number">1</span>, <span class="number">1</span>, <span class="number">2</span>)</span><br><span class="line">    dst_pts = np.float32([kp2[m.trainIdx].pt <span class="keyword">for</span> m <span class="keyword">in</span> topmatch]).reshape(-<span class="number">1</span>, <span class="number">1</span>, <span class="number">2</span>)</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    <span class="comment"># There is no separate RANSAC function in OpenCV, it is generally used in the findHomography function as a filter.</span></span><br><span class="line">    <span class="comment"># **Params: M is the Homography matrix, mask is a list of the feature points that match successfully.</span></span><br><span class="line">    <span class="comment">#           ransacReprojThreshold is a parameter of RANSAC</span></span><br><span class="line">    M, mask = cv2.findHomography(src_pts, dst_pts, cv2.RANSAC, ransacReprojThreshold)</span><br><span class="line">    matchesMask = mask.ravel().tolist()</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">else</span>:</span><br><span class="line">    matchesMask = <span class="literal">None</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment">#print(&#x27;Number of matching points after processing:&#x27;, len(matchesMask))</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">&#x27;&#x27;&#x27;</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">Part 5</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">Data visualization</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">&#x27;&#x27;&#x27;</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># Draw feature point matching image.</span></span><br><span class="line">draw_params = <span class="built_in">dict</span>(matchColor=-<span class="number">1</span>, singlePointColor=-<span class="number">1</span>, matchesMask=matchesMask, flags=<span class="number">2</span>)</span><br><span class="line">img_out = cv2.drawMatches(img_homo_rgb, kp1, img_homo_train_rgb, kp2, topmatch, <span class="literal">None</span>, **draw_params)</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># Display the result</span></span><br><span class="line">cv2.namedWindow(<span class="string">&#x27;BeforeRANSAC&#x27;</span>, <span class="number">0</span>)</span><br><span class="line">cv2.imshow(<span class="string">&#x27;BeforeRANSAC&#x27;</span>, BeforeRANSAC)</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">cv2.namedWindow(<span class="string">&#x27;AfterRANSAC&#x27;</span>, <span class="number">0</span>)</span><br><span class="line">cv2.imshow(<span class="string">&#x27;AfterRANSAC&#x27;</span>, img_out)</span><br><span class="line">cv2.waitKey(<span class="number">0</span>)</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">&#x27;&#x27;&#x27;</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">Part 6</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">Find the fundamental matrix and the essential matrix</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">&#x27;&#x27;&#x27;</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment">#Convert keypoints for findFundamentalMat function</span></span><br><span class="line">pts1 = np.int32(src_pts)</span><br><span class="line">pts2 = np.int32(dst_pts)</span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment">#TODO experiment with other methods for computing the fundamental matrix</span></span><br><span class="line">F, mask = cv2.findFundamentalMat(pts1,pts2,cv2.RANSAC)</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># Filter out the outlier points (mask.ravel()==1 gives us only the inlier points)</span></span><br><span class="line">pts1 = pts1[mask.ravel()==<span class="number">1</span>]</span><br><span class="line">pts2 = pts2[mask.ravel()==<span class="number">1</span>]</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment">#Calculate the essential matrix from the fundamental matrix E = K&#x27;^T.F.K</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment">#TODO get the real calibration matrix (I pass no camera matrix so it will default to identity matrix)</span></span><br><span class="line">E = cv2.findEssentialMat(pts1, pts2)</span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment">#TODO check the accuracy of the estimated fundamental matrix and essential matrix</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="built_in">print</span>(E)</span><br><span class="line"></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>收工！</p>]]></content>
      
      
